This paper deals with the design and analysis of a space-time block code (STBC) for wireless communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of communication systems. The paper also discusses the use of modulation schemes, which suggests that it could belong to cs.SI (Signal Processing), which deals with the processing of signals in communication systems. Additionally, the paper discusses the decoding complexity of the proposed STBC, which could place it in the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), which deals with the design and analysis of communication networks. The paper also discusses the performance of the proposed STBC in terms of power distribution and scalability, which could place it in the categories of cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), respectively.
